</div><br />
<br />
I don't think SOE really understands why we consider this a "fix" and not just wishful thinking. <br />
<br />
Please make a clear note that <b>all other resist debuffs</b> have always carried steep modifiers (or are totally unresistable), because the <b>very purpose of a debuff </b> is to weaken a mob's resistance to a certain type of affect to which it is otherwise <i>more</i> resistant than average. Our cold debuffs do not land on a mob that is even somewhat resistant to cold, which almost entirely defeats the purpose of this spell line.<br />
<br />
Also, for items that have been sitting at "currently being evaluated" status for multiple list submissions, could we request some distinction between items which have been approved for development, and items for which no decision has been made? If the latter, we need to know why.<br />
<br />
SOE has had more than enough time to "evaluate" some of these items and update their status so we can decide whether to make adjustments or replace them with other issues.<br />
<br />
~Firemynd</div>
