It's significant when you consider that devs automatically tend to suspect players of asking for more than is fair, and don't always spend enough time thinking about the numbers in front of them. I wouldn't want it left to chance that some idiot is going to blow us off because his 3 whole seconds of thoughtful consideration towards this issue will lead to a conclusion like, "800 mana sounds pretty good for 4k damage. Next.."<br />
<br />
~Firemynd</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
