	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>I realize that Lion's Stregth is a melee modifier similar to their 'increase damage' disciplines, but most non-hybrid offensive discs refresh quickly enough that meleers use them almost as soon as they pop (unlike defensive discs which they tend to save for emergenies). Some reset as frequently as 6 minutes. <br />
<br />
Even when your group only has two pure meleers, you could easily find yourself casting LS every 4-5 minutes, on one or the other; in addition to routine buffing of hybrids and others who want LS. Aside from the obvious hassle, this doesn't seem logical. It's hard to believe that a buff with a 1+ hour duration was intended to require such frequent rebuff maintenance. <br />
<br />
Furthermore, disciplines appear in their own buff window, not with spell buffs, so they shouldn't be overwriting ANY spell-based buffs. As far as I know, LS is the only spell buff currently being overwritten by melee discs.<br />
<br />
I'd conclude this is a bug.<br />
<br />
SOE should adjust the stacking code so the % modifiers from melee discs can supercede LS without causing the buff to disappear. <br />
<br />
~Firemynd</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
